        <p>If you’re a young OPOWER employee, there’s a good chance you’ll run into coworkers at DC’s various nightlife events. <a href="http://hirshhorn.si.edu/afterhours/" title="Hirshhorn After Hours">Hirshhorn After Hours</a> – a party at the Smithsonian’s contemporary art gallery – recently drew about 10 percent of OPOWER. And if there’s no organized event like that, you’ll find us attending gallery openings, dancing on U Street or catching a show at one of DC’s small, but renowned concert venues.</p>

        <p>Employees with families trade tips on school districts (the area has 16 of the top 100 high schools in the country) and favorite playgrounds (we’ve got more than 200,000 acres of parkland). At our company picnic, the kids of OPOWER competed in a hula hoop contest (which, embarrassingly, <a href="http://vimeo.com/14507524">Dan almost won</a>).</p>

        <p>Regardless of your status in life, you’ll find something enjoyable in the area and, chances are, you’ll find a coworker to do it with you. We’re outgoing, we’re friendly and we like to have fun. So whether it’s seeing a movie, training for the <a href="http://www.savagemantri.org/" title="Savage Man Triathlon">Savage Man Triathlon</a> or a babysitter recommendation, we’ll be there to help you out. </p>
    
